    Example datasets

Example datasets

Source: vignettes/quollr1sample.Rmd
quollr1sample.Rmd
library(cardinalR)
library(langevitour)

Examples of different data structures that can be generated are shown below.

Clustering data 

gau_data <- gau_clust(n = 500, num_clust = 5, 
mean_matrix = rbind(c(1,0,0,0), c(0,1,0,0), c(0,0,1,0), c(0,0,0,1), c(0,0,0,0)), 
var_vec = c(0.05, 0.05, 0.05, 0.05, 0.05), num_dims = 4, num_noise = 2, 
min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)

colnames(gau_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(gau_data))

langevitour(gau_data, pointSize = 2)

Grid data 

two_grd_data <- two_grid_comb_bkg(n_value = 15, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)
two_grd_data$n
#> [1] 585

colnames(two_grd_data$df) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(two_grd_data$df))

langevitour(two_grd_data$df, pointSize = 2)

Circular data 

curvy_cyc_data <- curvy_cycle(n = 300, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)

colnames(curvy_cyc_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(curvy_cyc_data))

langevitour(curvy_cyc_data, pointSize = 2)

Branching data 

tree_data <- tree(n = 490, num_noise = 2, 
min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)

colnames(tree_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(tree_data))

langevitour(tree_data, pointSize = 2)

Linear data 

four_linear_data <- four_long_clust(n = 500, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, 
                                    max_n = 0.05)

colnames(four_linear_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(four_linear_data))

langevitour(four_linear_data, pointSize = 2)

Nonlinear data 

two_curvy_panckakes <- two_curvy_panckakes(n = 300, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, 
                                           max_n = 0.05)

colnames(two_curvy_panckakes) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(two_curvy_panckakes))

langevitour(two_curvy_panckakes, pointSize = 2)

Sphere data 

sphere_data <- sphere(radius = 1, resolution = 20, num_noise = 2, 
                      min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)

colnames(sphere_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(sphere_data))

langevitour(sphere_data, pointSize = 2)

Mobius with Gaussian cluster 

mobius_clust_data <- mobius_clust(n = 500, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, 
                                  max_n = 0.05)

colnames(mobius_clust_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(mobius_clust_data))

langevitour(mobius_clust_data, pointSize = 2)

Triangular data 

train_3d_data <- tri_3d(n = 512, num_noise = 2, min_n = -0.05, max_n = 0.05)

colnames(train_3d_data) <- paste0("x", 1:NCOL(train_3d_data))

langevitour(train_3d_data, pointSize = 2)
